A GAME OF TWO HALVES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    My family was once divided by football - not in a shouting,
    chucking saucepans around kind of way - but more in a brittle
    chilliness that always seemed to settle over things when we all got
    together. It wasn't that we didn't love each other, we did, but the
    problem lay in the simple fact that the family was divided in its
    football loyalties.

